cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper discusses a generic approach to training deep models, specifically generative models, using one-element mini-batches. This is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and statistical learning (cs.SD). However, given the focus on image resolution and the use of deep networks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
